Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.27,0:06:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.68,0:06:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the distribution center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they all messengers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.02,0:06:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.71,0:06:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We collect items that people post across the fleet, and we hand them in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.24,0:06:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we get delivery jobs in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.27,0:06:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.73,0:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.36,0:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Melty! Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the work?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.46,0:06:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotten the hang of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm learning bit by bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.96,0:06:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With Amy as your mentor, \Nyou'll pick it up in a flash!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.96,0:06:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got afternoon deliveries!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.61,0:06:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing we can \Nsplit it three ways, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.43,0:06:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since \Nwe all got the same area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.77,0:07:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So then he asked me, "What present \Nwould a girl like you be happy with?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.23,0:07:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love some new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.37,0:07:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine are always wearing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the point! \NDoes he have to ask {\i1}me{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.91,0:07:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit inconsiderate, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.62,0:07:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.83,0:07:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you just ignore him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy for you to say with \Na boyfriend waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.58,0:07:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.66,0:07:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All done!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.72,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if we split it up like this, \Nit makes things much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.42,0:07:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.22,0:07:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.84,0:07:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not too familiar with \Nthe ships in this area yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.50,0:07:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,These ships are from the fleet I \Njoined with, so I know them well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.18,0:07:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.72,0:08:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Looks good to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.40,0:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.32,0:08:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! That's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.25,0:08:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no place for amateurs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mayta!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.90,0:08:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema, you shouldn't bother them \Nwhen they're working.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.12,0:08:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.55,0:08:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you an engineer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.54,0:08:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.36,0:09:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do you build this part?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.98,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the composition of the alloy? \NWhat torque of actuator do you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.77,0:09:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're that keen on machines, \Nyou should come and work with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.71,0:09:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use all the help we can get!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.48,0:09:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it right there, Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Mr. Pompadour!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pompadour...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.11,0:09:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But for now, I'd like to \Nlearn more about Gargantia!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.03,0:09:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.33,0:09:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job finding this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we can pull it up again in one piece.{might need a devil fruit??}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.90,0:09:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been short on ships \Never since taking in Kugel's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.18,0:09:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.08,0:09:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would we put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We can harvest the Chrono's farms early.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.32,0:10:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.22,0:10:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.01,0:10:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This'll be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.91,0:10:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.20,0:10:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.59,0:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! I'm drenched in sweat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.09,0:10:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, a bath after work is a gift from the heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.92,0:10:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ledo. I heard they decided to \Npull up the wrecked ship you found.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.73,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.82,0:11:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I last \Ngot to use my secret weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.15,0:11:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Secret weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.43,0:11:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! It's quite a show, \Nso look forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema showed me around the Kugel fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty organized for your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.73,0:11:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"For your age," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She's only a year younger than you, Melty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's here, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.41,0:11:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.83,0:11:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, Ledo was the real MVP today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.55,0:11:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.20,0:11:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't say anything about it to me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.49,0:11:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you came together again? \NGlad to see you're getting along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.94,0:11:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Gargantia sure has an impressive \Nassortment of facilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.18,0:11:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! A marine mix for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.98,0:11:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's the ex-pirate queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.79,0:12:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn some respect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's "pirate queen on vacation" to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.53,0:12:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She calls herself that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My break's almost over, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.03,0:12:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing a big salvage op soon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.91,0:12:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been tasked with clearing \Nthe area so no one gets in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.17,0:12:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the muscle of the fleet, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.47,0:12:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you {\i1}do{\i0} work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.76,0:12:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.95,0:12:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Leema. Amy's showing me the ropes at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.81,0:12:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a messenger?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.37,0:12:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna hear your stories!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.35,0:12:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me about the \Nflying Yunboro you rode in!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:12:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.56,0:13:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.76,0:13:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a machine built to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He used gravity manipulation to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.63,0:13:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He could understand any language,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and he used the immense power \Nat his disposal to protect his pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.58,0:13:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate battle armor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.65,0:13:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a Machine Caliber.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.97,0:13:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.87,0:13:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So he really was the same as \Nthe sky god's divine messenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.12,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sky god?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.12,0:13:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean Colonel Kugel's Striker?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.48,0:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm from Lord Kugel's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.61,0:13:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you tell me what happened to the Colonel and Striker?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.78,0:14:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutie spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this? Do I see someone flirting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Two-timing, even?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't say I blame you, Leema.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.36,0:14:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo, girls need constant attention, \Nor they start to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.63,0:14:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep! And that goes for Amy too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.81,0:14:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how she'd always \Nask Chamber for advice in secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, is there something Ledo would, \Nyou know, like to have?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.85,0:14:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.89,0:14:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The food and other supplies necessary \Nfor the Lieutenant's daily operation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are already provided to him on a steady basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, like, something that'll \Nmake him happy or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.50,0:14:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, something that'll \Nmake him go "wow!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.67,0:15:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It has already been ascertained that the Alliance's recreation program
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.42,0:15:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is ineffective on the Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.95,0:15:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.82,0:15:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I get to know Ledo better?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.70,0:15:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How do you know about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.52,0:15:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just advice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.18,0:15:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.66,0:15:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A lovers' spat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be nice to be young.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.17,0:15:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm almost jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.28,0:15:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo, I'm glad to see you're \Ndoing so well for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.52,0:15:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but work's important too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.63,0:15:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvaging's one thing, but have you \Ngotten a taste for engineering yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.21,0:15:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Pinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been teaching me a bit \Nabout how Yunboros work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.74,0:15:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.98,0:15:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I just felt sorry for him, taking orders from a wreckage freak all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.56,0:15:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling a wreckage freak?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:15:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:15:59.27,Alt,,0,0,0,,Leema.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.27,0:16:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.66,0:16:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always wondered how the \NColonel's fleet turned out the way it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.47,0:16:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.34,0:16:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My home ship joined the fleet back when Lord Kugel and his messenger began guiding the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.04,0:16:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The fleet was united by the worship \Nof the sky god's emissary, Lord Kugel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.75,0:16:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the whalesquids were defeated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and Priestesses Linaria and Aleria \Npassed away, everything changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.30,0:16:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave everything we had to sustain the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.12,0:16:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even dying was just seen \Nas another way to contribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.22,0:16:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"To stay strong, dispose of the weak."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.44,0:17:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Convince those who can't fight
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that sacrificing themselves for the good of the group is the greatest joy."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.20,0:17:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the way of the \NGalactic Alliance of Humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.72,0:17:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it hard to believe that the \NColonel would have wanted that, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.21,0:17:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No one even knows exactly \Nwhen Lord Kugel lost his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.78,0:17:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If he'd still been alive, \NI'm certain we would have found a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.22,0:17:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I owed my life to him many times over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.26,0:17:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been able to find anything of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not easy to find out more about Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.18,0:17:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.83,0:17:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I hoped we could find out more from the ejected cockpit that remained,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.82,0:18:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but the technology used is far beyond \Neven that of the ancients.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the scriptures my sister Linaria inherited from our father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.80,0:18:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry that we couldn't be of help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.16,0:18:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true at all. There is so much in these books that we of Gargantia did not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.30,0:18:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity realized that their \Nplanet's days were numbered,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.80,0:18:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and most joined one of two rivaling factions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But some, few in number as they were, \Ndecided to look for another path.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.21,0:18:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We are the descendants of those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All of humanity tried to survive in any way they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.74,0:18:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who left for the stars amidst that conflict must have felt the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.38,0:18:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They abandoned Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.37,0:18:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I'd like to believe it was a \Ndifficult decision for them to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.82,0:19:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what happened to the people who left Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only one here who does.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.13,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be something I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.12,0:19:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to find a way to \Ncommunicate with the whalesquids.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.18,0:19:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There might be a better way for \Nus to live, without conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.16,0:19:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just trying to make amends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.64,0:19:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.50,0:19:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you feel responsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.16,0:19:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, I live in fear every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.21,0:19:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.00,0:20:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alliance is still fighting an \Nall-out war with the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.38,0:20:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And deep inside, I actually feel like it's a necessary war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.99,0:20:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But... You're here with us now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The galactic war you came from \Nis far, far away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.15,0:20:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not relevant anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.72,0:20:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's very relevant. Everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.48,0:20:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything humanity does, \Nbe it here or there, is connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.93,0:20:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ever came into conflict with the whalesquids,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.22,0:20:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or if the Hideauze found Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.73,0:20:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,would I be able to handle it \Ndifferently from the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.05,0:20:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I find another way?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.79,0:20:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I couldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.58,0:20:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I too had to throw away \Nsomething precious just to stay alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.08,0:21:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.34,0:21:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't come down to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.71,0:21:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd find a way. Just like back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.42,0:21:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Chamber did so much \Nto help us during that huge storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.89,0:21:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The huge storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.45,0:21:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema, you were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.44,0:21:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't intend to—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, yes I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.89,0:21:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me what happened with \NLedo and Chamber in that storm!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.11,0:22:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the boats got torn loose \Nand dashed against the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.33,0:22:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Check for leaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The bulkheads are closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.08,0:22:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! But check anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.90,0:22:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.70,0:22:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Over to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.01,0:22:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger! Moving along!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.69,0:22:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Secured!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.15,0:22:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Pull the crane!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.60,0:22:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Connection complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.81,0:22:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.64,0:22:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job, Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.54,0:23:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.90,0:23:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.12,0:23:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Altemia's interlocks are damaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.56,0:23:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.59,0:23:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.72,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The support wires have all snapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.97,0:23:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the interlock pylons are damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.58,0:23:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one is left.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.43,0:23:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.44,0:23:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Both engines have failed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.10,0:23:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Commodore, more than five hundred \Npeople live aboard the Altemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.77,0:23:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They are in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.89,0:23:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Any bridges?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.29,0:23:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one left, but it could break any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.09,0:23:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we repair the interlocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.18,0:23:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have the manpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.79,0:23:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediate repairs are out of question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.36,0:24:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Urgent delivery!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.79,0:24:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a damage report!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.82,0:24:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Allowing such a large ship to drift freely \Nwould put the entire fleet at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.06,0:24:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We will scuttle the Altemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.38,0:24:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Altemia?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.91,0:24:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.83,0:24:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All personnel on the Altemia are to \Nevacuate immediately! Top priority!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.49,0:24:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Scuttle the Altemia!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.73,0:24:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuate it right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.19,0:24:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Saya's ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.36,0:24:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.32,0:24:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.54,0:24:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.84,0:24:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Saya?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.37,0:25:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She isn't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.55,0:25:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.20,0:25:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a chance! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.12,0:25:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If she's to sink, I'm going down with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.12,0:25:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, stop being a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.20,0:25:19.12,Alt,,0,0,0,,I won't leave the ship I've lived my life on!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.89,0:25:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.14,0:25:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.30,0:25:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.84,0:25:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister will oversee the evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.73,0:25:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys leave too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.40,0:25:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fleiss!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.06,0:25:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't steer her anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.16,0:25:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point staying on the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.84,0:25:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.86,0:25:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bridge here!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.85,0:25:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.25,0:25:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The central tower's empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.26,0:25:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! I'm the only one on the bridge too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.49,0:25:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry with the rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.39,0:25:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.84,0:25:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.40,0:25:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.21,0:25:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.47,0:25:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the ship's being scuttled, so I was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.97,0:26:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just making sure no one's been left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.28,0:26:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help. What areas are left?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.14,0:26:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The forecastle and the sterncastle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.05,0:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll check the forecastle, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.93,0:26:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.04,0:26:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that we're abandoning the Altemia?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.14,0:26:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.10,0:26:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're evacuating now!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.81,0:26:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they gonna be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.24,0:26:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anyone still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.15,0:26:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuate now!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.28,0:26:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.35,0:26:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You go ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.31,0:26:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.77,0:26:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.87,0:26:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.26,0:26:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.10,0:26:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We're done!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.21,0:26:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.75,0:26:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.29,0:26:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's scuttle her and get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.94,0:26:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really the only way?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.99,0:26:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroying the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.98,0:27:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She can't be steered anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.92,0:27:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And with only one interlock left, \Nshe could smash into the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.15,0:27:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to sink her before it comes to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.12,0:27:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born and raised here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.73,0:27:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never even heard of a storm this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.47,0:27:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some things in life \Nthat are simply beyond our control.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.30,0:27:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Altemia!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.38,0:27:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a huge wave coming! Get out of there right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.11,0:27:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Melty? I can't hear you properly!{idk it seemed pretty audible to me}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.27,0:27:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Say it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.01,0:27:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.70,0:27:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.91,0:28:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.65,0:28:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.40,0:28:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.56,0:28:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.76,0:28:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.15,0:28:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Detecting an abnormal angle \Nof inclination among the ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.50,0:28:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.32,0:28:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy! Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.65,0:28:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.34,0:28:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.46,0:28:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.05,0:29:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're close to capsizing!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.30,0:29:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber! Maximum output!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.72,0:29:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.70,0:29:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, kiddo!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.11,0:29:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold her!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.45,0:29:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.81,0:29:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, reel it in!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.28,0:29:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.72,0:29:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.19,0:29:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look over there! We've got trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.57,0:29:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.58,0:29:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do now, Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.42,0:29:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency broadcast intercepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.26,0:30:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.79,0:30:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Altemia's broken loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.93,0:30:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Saya and Amy are still on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.52,0:30:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.55,0:30:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The vessel in question has lost both its engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.68,0:30:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It is most likely out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.37,0:30:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's adrift?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.97,0:30:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.90,0:30:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.24,0:30:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't move from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.23,0:30:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Straighten up, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.05,0:30:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.05,0:30:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo, metalhead...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.31,0:30:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back inside and put these on!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.52,0:30:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.49,0:30:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap, we're drifting back!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.78,0:31:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hull recovering.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.72,0:31:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She's back! She stopped listing!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.52,0:31:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Declination returning to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.74,0:31:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Balance is likely to be restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.38,0:31:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.92,0:31:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.46,0:32:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Threat level lowering.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.79,0:32:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.30,0:32:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I only managed thanks to Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.76,0:32:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.50,0:32:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure even if something like that happened now,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.78,0:32:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.70,0:32:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You've always done everything you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.65,0:32:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.44,0:33:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Time to go down!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.59,0:33:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellows! The capture beacon is lowering at a steady pace!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.69,0:33:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.75,0:33:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You all hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.07,0:33:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna raise a ship from her grave!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.90,0:33:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a treasure among treasures!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.00,0:33:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift her well!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.95,0:33:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.91,0:33:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Recheck the area!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.94,0:34:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinion! Letter for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.11,0:34:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.92,0:34:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You don't have any more deliveries?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.69,0:34:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I saved this one for last.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.32,0:34:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You're worried about Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.58,0:34:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.25,0:34:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.12,0:34:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinion! The anchors!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.23,0:34:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.35,0:34:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready, guys?{PUT YA GUNS ON}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.49,0:34:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get this done!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.68,0:34:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Team one! Attach the guide wires to the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.21,0:35:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Team two! Pull the main wires under the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.99,0:35:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm connection!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.95,0:35:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.62,0:35:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to finish the job. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.45,0:35:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.39,0:35:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.36,0:35:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My wire got stuck on something!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.83,0:35:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.91,0:35:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's collapsing!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.08,0:35:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of there! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.96,0:36:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead! I've got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.34,0:36:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.94,0:36:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.88,0:36:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo went under!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.00,0:36:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.84,0:36:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Disconnect your cable!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.53,0:36:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.85,0:36:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.50,0:37:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How much air is left?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.79,0:37:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.48,0:37:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Open reserve tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.05,0:37:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency injection of CO2 absorbent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.74,0:37:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm battery power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.37,0:37:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Manipulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.51,0:37:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Comms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.64,0:37:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.26,0:37:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the communications cable...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.73,0:37:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone respond! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.64,0:38:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened down there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.05,0:38:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.47,0:38:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a sudden burst of gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.34,0:38:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole place collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.96,0:38:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Ledo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.42,0:38:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he's alive, his air won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.20,0:38:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then hurry up and dig him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.26,0:38:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's far too dangerous to go down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.86,0:38:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The rescue party would get buried too.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.23,0:38:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.72,0:38:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.40,0:38:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you do {\i1}something{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.98,0:38:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellows!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.62,0:38:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellows! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.10,0:38:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No response.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.74,0:39:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Second Lieutenant Ledo, \Npilot of Machine Caliber K6821! Anyone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.40,0:39:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No response.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.68,0:39:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It is likely that the Hideauze attack \Nleft them adrift with their reactor exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.45,0:39:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and restore communications!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.61,0:39:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You useless piece of junk!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.92,0:39:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It is advised that you refrain from radio transmissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.72,0:39:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.94,0:39:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Multiple Hideauze life-signs detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.94,0:39:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They might notice this unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.12,0:39:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.98,0:39:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I should just wait to be eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.60,0:39:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Activate the emergency beacon!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.67,0:39:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't leave these decisions up to a machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.82,0:39:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.20,0:39:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As the pilot, you have final call on all decisions, \NSecond Lieutenant Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.46,0:39:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose to exercise that prerogative \Nand use your own judgment,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.64,0:39:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I will reevaluate the situation \Nand suggest the best possible course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.87,0:40:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So your power depends on me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.07,0:40:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.92,0:40:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I await your judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.52,0:40:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.98,0:40:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to die here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.57,0:40:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are gonna survive, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.69,0:40:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.57,0:40:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I am an interface system that supports \Nand oversees the development of pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.39,0:40:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I exist solely to set you up for success.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.60,0:40:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right. Survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.95,0:40:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He told me I should trust myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.37,0:40:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And he told me he would trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.45,0:40:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.03,0:40:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.77,0:40:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.89,0:41:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.17,0:41:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone who can dive, get in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.83,0:41:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not enough air cylinders! \NScrape together all we've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.44,0:41:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.73,0:42:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather the ship captains.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.52,0:42:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask them to supply us \Nwith manpower and resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.22,0:42:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the medics on standby too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.63,0:42:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.21,0:42:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.68,0:42:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go save him!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.87,0:42:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.61,0:42:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.38,0:42:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.32,0:42:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.16,0:42:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.69,0:42:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.32,0:42:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.62,0:42:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You have other things you need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.82,0:42:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When these daredevils come back, we need you to greet them with a smile on your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.39,0:42:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure we get out alive. All of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.08,0:42:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.33,0:43:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.72,0:43:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.08,0:43:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They still haven't found him?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.22,0:43:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Rackage?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.71,0:43:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you useless fools even doing?{i'd put landlubbers, but...}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.69,0:43:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Make way!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.48,0:43:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.48,0:44:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to say, but no one is \Nallowed to die on my watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.00,0:44:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Rackage?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.00,0:44:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.74,0:44:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of this gap!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.37,0:44:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Amico!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.57,0:44:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Stronzo!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.02,0:44:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.58,0:44:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up, Rackage!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.42,0:44:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.38,0:44:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.88,0:44:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.29,0:45:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"I rerouted the compressed air \Nfrom the floaters into the cabin."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.35,0:45:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're quite something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.35,0:45:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.37,0:45:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll force the gap open together.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.25,0:45:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment we do, \Ndetach the limbs and the floaters.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.93,0:45:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We only get one chance at this.{you only chance once}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.73,0:45:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.51,0:45:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.43,0:45:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll count down from three!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.50,0:45:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.69,0:45:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.90,0:45:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.11,0:45:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.84,0:45:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.26,0:45:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.01,0:46:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The machine's free!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.11,0:46:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.59,0:46:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.20,0:46:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.48,0:46:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness he's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.85,0:46:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.72,0:46:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.32,0:47:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad you're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.64,0:47:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.13,0:47:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.01,0:49:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Proceed to the next phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.58,0:49:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{space language}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.24,0:49:45.99,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}kore made wa betsu no michi ayundekita futari
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.24,0:49:45.99,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}We used to walk different paths
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.99,0:49:52.00,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}onaji jikan wo kizamihajimeta n da
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.99,0:49:52.00,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}Now our time together has begun
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.00,0:49:58.63,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}taisetsu na takaramono katachi wa mienai kedo
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.00,0:49:58.63,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}The truly important things are invisible to the eye
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.63,0:50:04.99,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}te wo tsunaidara fureta ki ga shita
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.63,0:50:04.99,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I think I know what matters when I touch your hand
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.99,0:50:11.16,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}kimi no hitomi ni utsuru atarashii keshiki
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.99,0:50:11.16,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I want to know what the future will be like
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.16,0:50:19.63,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}dare yori chikaku de watashi mo issho ni mitsumetai
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.16,0:50:19.63,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I want to hear it directly from you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.63,0:50:25.90,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}oboeteite ne itsumo soba ni iru yo
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.63,0:50:25.90,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}Remember, I'm right here
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.90,0:50:32.21,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}kore kara mo kimi ga kaeru basho de itai kara
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.90,0:50:32.21,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I want to be there when you return
